<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Eastern Cape MEC of Sport, Dr Pemmy Majodina, says the province is ready to deliver an awards ceremony that will make not only the boxing community, but the entire country proud.“The Eastern Cape is  proud to be the hosts of these prestigious boxing awards in the friendly city of Port Elizabeth in the Nelson Mandela Metro, during this year’s centenary celebrations of Madiba (Nelson Mndela) himself. “This province has produced world renowned boxers and we are more than ready to stage this year’s edition of the awards.“It is worth noting as well, that even when boxing was experiencing a dry season in terms of support, the Eastern Cape continued to be a leading province in making sure that boxing tournaments are well attended in large numbers, because the Eastern Cape community loves boxing. “I congratulate all the nominees. It is through your hard work and passion that all your efforts will be recognised.” Unsurprisingly, a number of the nominees for major awards are from the Eastern Cape.BSA CEO Tsholofelo Lejaka says he is satisfied with the preparations so far. Lejaka thanked the Eastern Cape government for its co-operation.“We have formed a great partnership with the Eastern Cape Department of Sport,   have been working closely for the last couple of weeks in planning the 2017 Boxing Awards. We are satisfied with the progress made. There is a lot that still needs to happen between now and tomorrow night, but we are confident that we will deliver a great show,” Lejaka said. The categories of Male Boxer of the Year and Female Boxer of the Year in particular are hotly contested, and both feature a star-studded lineup.Zolani Tete, Azinga Fuzile, Thulani Mbenge and Kevin Lerena are up for Male Boxer of the Year, while Prudends Mapule Ngubane, BukiweN onina and Noni Tenge have been nominated as Female Boxer of the Year.Like this story? Get the free Daily Kick App today and stay on top of your game with only the best from SunSport, Soccer Laduma, KickOff and many more!ALL YOUR SOCCER AND NEWS IN ONE PLACE THATHA ZONKE